<TITLE> Hasina for re-establishing people's voting right </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 7 (bdnews24.com)Awami League president Sheikh Hasina Thursday emphasised the country would not achieve any advancement until people get back their rights to vote and speak and overall transparency and accountability ensured. The AL president said so while talking to reporters after offering flowers at the portrait of Bangabandhu marking the historical Six-point Charter. "I hope people will get back the franchise, retain and exercise basic human rights and their rights to practicing democracy. People will vote their own representatives to power so that their basic rights are protected," Hasina said. She said, " People of Bangladesh would like to see their rights established in a society where transparency and accountability prevail." Earlier, Sheikh Hasina offered flowers at Bangabandhu's portrait at the Bangabandhu Memorial Museum in Dhanmandi and observed a minute's silence showing respect to the 11 martyrs who had laid their lives to realise the 6-point charter. AL presidium members Syeda Sajeda Chowdhury, Abdur Razzak, Tofael Ahmed, Suranjit Sengupta and Begum Matia Chowdhury were present on the occasion. Strict security measures were clamped around the venue on Dhanmandi road 32 on the occasion. No pedestrians even were allowed to use the road running in front of the place during the stay of the AL president and her entourage there. Four-five representatives from each AL organic bodies were allowed to offer flowers at the memorial. bdnews2
